# 🫀 Heart Disease Prediction using Machine Learning

## Project Overview
Heart disease is one of the leading causes of death worldwide. This project applies machine learning techniques to predict the likelihood of heart disease using the Cleveland Heart Disease dataset.

### Objectives
- Analyze patient medical data
- Build predictive machine learning models
- Compare model performance
- Evaluate using standard metrics
2. Import Libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import joblib

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, GridSearchCV
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.impute import SimpleImputer
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier

from sklearn.metrics import (
    accuracy_score,
    classification_report,
    confusion_matrix,
    roc_auc_score,
    RocCurveDisplay
)

3. Load Dataset
df = pd.read_csv("heart.csv")
df.head()

4. Dataset Information
df.shape
df.info()
df.describe()
df.isnull().sum()

5. Exploratory Data Analysis
Target Distribution
plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
sns.countplot(x='target', data=df)
plt.title("Target Distribution")
plt.show()
Correlation Heatmap
